According to the user-defined \"trailing amount\", the trailing stop price moves together with the market price, and the stop price is continuously recalculated with a fixed amount lower than the market price. \\nTrailing stop price = market price-trailing amount; When a stop loss order is triggered, the limit order price = trailing stop price - price spread\\n\\nAssuming the market price is 125, set the trailing amount to 5. The specified spread is 0.5. When the stock price rises all the way to 135 and then drops to 130 (at this moment trailing stop price = 135-5), the stop loss order is triggered and an on order with a price of 129.5 (order price = 130-0.5) will be automatically submitted.

A measure of the risk profile of your account. The risk control status is divided into 4 levels: Safe, Medium, Warning, and Dangerous.\\n\\nSafe: No Financing.\\n\\nMedium: Financing has been used, total asset value is above initial margin requirement, based on the current leverage level, the higher the leverage, the higher the risk.\\n\\nWarning: Total asset value is below initial margin requirement but still above maintenance margin. At the moment, purchasing power has been exhausted and no new positions can be opened; please pay attention to market changes to prevent margin calls in the account.\\n\\nDanger: Total asset value is below maintenance margin requirement. In this case, you must deposit to fulfill margin call before 15:00 on the same day according to the \\\"Margin Call Amount\\\" or take the initiative to close some positions to lower your risk level. Otherwise, your positions will be forced liquidated to fulfill Margin Call. The broker has the discretion as to the stock, price and volume put up for sell at anytime after cut-off time on force-selling day. Please pay attention to indicators such as risk control status and leverage.\\n\\nEquity Balance：The sum of cash balance and total market value of the stocks held.\\n\\nInitial Margin：The margin required for financing transactions is calculated according to a certain percentage of the market value of the stocks held. When the total asset value is less than the initial margin requirement, the purchasing power is exhausted and new positions cannot be opened.\\n\\nMaintenance Margin：Maintenance margin requirement = account holdings market value × account holding asset maintenance margin ratio. When the total asset value is less than the maintenance margin requirement, the account will be \\\"dangerous\\\" status, and some stocks need to be liquidated or further deposit is required.

A measure of the risk profile of your account. The risk control status is divided into 4
        levels: Safe, Medium, Warning, and Dangerous.\n\nSafe: No Financing.\n\nMedium: Financing has been used, total
        asset value is above initial margin requirement, based on the current leverage level, the higher the leverage,
        the higher the risk.\n\nWarning: Total asset value is below initial margin requirement but still above
        maintenance margin. At the moment, purchasing power has been exhausted and no new positions can be opened;
        please pay attention to market changes to prevent margin calls in the account.\n\nDanger: Total asset value is
        below maintenance margin requirement. In this case, you must deposit to fulfill margin call before 15:00 on the
        same day according to the \"Margin Call Amount\" or take the initiative to close some positions to lower your
        risk level. Otherwise, your positions will be forced liquidated to fulfill Margin Call. The broker has the
        discretion as to the stock, price and volume put up for sell at anytime after cut-off time on force-selling day.
        Please pay attention to indicators such as risk control status and leverage.
